The Deputy Majority Leader in the Senate, Senator Bala Na’Allah has won the Kebbi South Senatorial election. Announcing the result on Monday, INEC’s Returning Officer, Professor Ibrahim Zagga said Na’Allah got 136,187 votes to defeat his PDP opponent, Chief Benjamin Dikki who polled 62,733 votes in the election. Na'Allah defeats 4 other contenders to clinch Kebbi South senatorial ticket Kogi: Na’Allah carpets PDP over call for AGF resignation Senatorial primary: Na'Allah wins APC ticket